  "prompt": "Typically how many clients do massage spas serve per month at an average sized location?",
  "response": "The number of clients that an average-sized massage spa serves per month can vary widely depending on several factors such as location, the reputation of the spa, the types of services offered, and local demand. However, a rough estimate for an average-sized spa in a moderately busy area might range from 200 to 600 clients per month.\n\nTo break it down further:\n- If the spa has around 6-10 therapists working full-time and each therapist can handle around 3-5 clients per day, the spa might serve 18-50 clients per day.\n- Over the course of a month, assuming an average of 25 working days, this would translate to approximately 450 to 1,250 client sessions per month.\n\nThese numbers can fluctuate based on seasonal trends, special promotions, membership programs, and other marketing efforts.",
